<br>
I plan to join the FV playing community soon, and I'm in the process of determining which class to play. =)<br>
<br>
What is the current state of the &quot;melee vs. caster&quot; balance on Firiona Vie?   Are weapons like Centi swords, etc commonly available to level 20-45ish players?<br>
(On most of the standard ruleset servers, such as Druzzil Ro, the saturation of these kinds of weapons has completely ruined any relative caster vs melee balance IMO).<br>
<br>
Any information or feedback on the current state of FV is appreciated.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uarios.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Arios</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 794<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/12/02 10:49:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2140.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Relative caster vs melee balance on FV?</span><hr size=1> Play what ever you enjoy.<br>
<br>
There are alot less second character twinks here so there are less suped up you ng melees.<br>
<br>
But who really cares about this caster vs melee balance. If you are on a team with said melee you kill faster so . . . <br>
<br>
Casters never really get that weak, they might (oh gosh) end up only a small number of times more powerful than a melee but it really never gets that bad.<br>
<br>
Okay so a warrior lvl 1 with full cobalt or better is going to do better for a while than say a mage.<br>
<br>
By 20? the warrior has not changed in power but the mage has. At that point *tosses a coin*<br>
<br>
As I first said though, play what you enjoy not what makes power gaming sense. Mind you if all you like is power gaming then maybe find which class is most powerful <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  in which case on FV I would go caster. Then again what definition of power are you using?<br>
<br>
Solo?<br>
Group?<br>
Raid?<br>
<br>
Enjoy what ever you choose.<br>
<br>
Personaly though if you are a roxor suxor sort of chappy please go somewhere else :-)<br>
<br>
