Proud member of Lux Aeternam</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uvartis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vartis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/12/02 11:39:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2140.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> twinks eh?</span><hr size=1> Thanks for the reply.  Although I'm a bit more interested in the state of FV &quot;mudflation&quot; than advice on what to play ; )  And I'm not a &quot;rox0r sux0r l33t d3wd&quot; (ouch, my brain hurts now).<br>
<br>
I've played casters, priests and melee on the regular servers from the last phase of the beta up until recently.<br>
The ability to get a group and enjoy playing what one likes playing can be heavily affected by how prevalent these kinds of weapons are available, especially in the mid-levels.  But, that discussion has been covered many times over on many other boards.<br>
<br>
Maybe I should rephrase my question slightly --<br>
<br>
What sort of weapons/gear does the average mid level melee (around level 30 - 35) player have on Firiona Vie?<br>
<br>
Thanks to all for the replies. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=traxxus>Traxxus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 218<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/12/02 12:09:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2140.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: twinks eh?</span><hr size=1> I'm a level 30 ranger. I don't have a regular group, so I fight in alot of pickup groups. Since I've been playing I've only seen two centi longswords. One when I was 18, the character weilding it was dark blue to me. The other when I was 20, the weilder was in his 40's. I've been fighting with an icetooth claw and a storfeather talon for about 8 levels now.  Most weapons I see melee's with are right around, if not slightly above their level. I see alot of BABS, and BALS, PGT's, WoFS, and SSOM's. I haven't seen many characters &lt;30 weilding weapons worth more than 500pp. Not to say I'm the greatest example, but I find it difficult to keep over 250pp at a time in the bank.<br>
<br>
As far as Armor, I'm a ranger so when I see someone in plate, well it's all just plate to me. I've seen few at my level with a full set of Ivy etched. My own armor is a mishmash of ivy etched, blackened alloy, banded, and ry'gor. It suits me well, but is certainly nothing astounding.<br>
<br>
I don't think the server population in general has grown high enough to cause pp devaluation and mass inflation. Either that or we just have a great group of very considerate highlevels who are taking care not to flood the market with platinum and planar gear.<br>
<br>
Good hunting,<br>
-Traxxus <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubraellarth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Braellarth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 91<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/12/02 12:11:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2140.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Melee vs caster</span><hr size=1> Because the average player only has one account there is no need to hunt items for there alts, wich means less people soloing.<br>
<br>
Guilds now only have to 'farm' items once unless for sale, and farming items is now a lot harder because of TLC.. wich means you often have to go into a spot of wealth at a lower lv so that you can stay there longer before TLC kicks in.<br>
<br>
This forces people into dungeons 'while' they are still a reasonable challenge so that all the party/guild/friends can get those items.<br>
As a result of this and now certain no-drop items are now dropable.. you see a 'lot' of lower lv quality wepons on the market instead... because the guild/friends rack up these items en-mass there is no one to give them to.. so often they go for sale.<br>
<br>
Will you see really cheep Centi swords? no. But there is bound to be something more in your lv range and at a more affordable price.<br>
<br>
Fleshripper/painbringer - are a item that you wont see much on other servers, they are no-drop but on here you can happily trade them out.. the great thing is that these items no longer rot when that warrior or shadowknight has them.. instead somone else can loot and give/trade/sell it.. so purely because of this you will see those nice two wepons on the market more than other servers.. and they are fun to play with the AOE.<br>
<br>
If that makes any sence to you. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uarios.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Arios</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 798<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(6/12/02 1:09:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2140.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Melee vs caster</span><hr size=1> There are large ranges of folks at 30 and the weapons and armor they have. You will see folks with aweful equipment (weapons and armor aweful and I mean raw hide still *grin*) but they are happy RPing and fighting away.<br>
<br>
You get folks who know the market and buy and sell and have nice stuff.<br>
<br>
So it depends how you play.<br>
<br>
I would suggest though that unless you are a very social person you might want a class that can solo if it has to. If you are obbsesively social and keep a heathy friends list you will get groups aah damn I keep forgeting, of course if you are a wiz or druid you can move to the group you are joining more easily ;-)<br>
<br>
